Yes, it's a good idea, then, to bring major money.  7 to 10k is a reasonable sum, especially if you're not planning to work right away.  The majority of that money will go for initial apartment costs, and possibly an initial phone connection (which can cost up to $700 for the initial installation).<br>
<br>
THe fellow who started the thread might be satisfied with a considerably shorter homestay, I thought, so I suggested an informal homestay.<br>
